e careful with ClassLoader.getResourceAsStream when using a leading slash. It’s necessary because our findResource will match \\\"/META-INF/MANIFEST.MF\\\". Once I have that, I can open the stream on the URL to the temporary manifest, which seems straightforward. I think I'll implement a dedicated file with a single test titled `sealedManifestUsesTypeResourceUrlAsSealBase`. That should help ensure everything is working as expected!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_rKapaNzguvzbjPCXLVOfdl5j|fc_0f8bad7776be2094016a256f8c6664819798050e5ac711505c", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.bytebuddy/byte-buddy/1.8.15/src/test/java/net_bytebuddy/byte_buddy/ByteArrayClassLoaderTest.java", "limit": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2262, "output": 1711, "cacheRead": 18944, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22917, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780838242569, "responseId": "resp_0f8bad7776be2094016a256f62ffb48197873d9886030ce1e3"}}
